###############################################################
# Generating thrift cpp source
###############################################################
Currently tajo-cpp-client is generated by thrift-0.9.2.
If you want to use the other thrift version, use the following command:
  $ ${THRIFT_HOME}/bin/thrift --gen cpp -o ${TAJO_HOME}/tajo-cpp-client/src/main \
    ${TAJO_HOME}/tajo-thrift-server/src/main/resources/thrift/tajo.thrift

###############################################################
# Build instruction for tajo-odbc
###############################################################
Requirements:
  - Thrift 0.9.2 or higher
    Not only compiler, but also cpp library
  - g++

Building with maven:
  $ cd $TAJO_SRC_ROOT/tajo-cpp-client
  $ mvn compile -DskipTests -Ptajo-cpp -Dthrift.home=/usr/local/thrift-0.9.2
  $ mvn test -DskipTests -Ptajo-cpp -Dthrift.home=/usr/local/thrift-0.9.2
  $ sudo cp ./src/main/cpp/tajo_*.h /usr/local/include/.
  $ sudo cp ./target/tajoclient/lib/* /usr/local/lib/.

Building with make:
  - The following environment variable required:
    . THRIFT_HOME

  $ cd $TAJO_SRC_ROOT/tajo-cpp-client
  $ export THRIFT_HOME=/usr/local/thrift-0.9.2
  $ make clean
  $ make
  $ ls -al target/tajoclient/lib
  $ make install

  - Currently changing install directory is not supported.
    You can change install directory by modifying INSTALL_PATH variable in Makefile.

When compiling there are many warnings "'htonll' macro redefined" on OsX, but this is not a problem.
This is thrift-0.9.2 bug and fixed thrift-0.9.3. If you want to resolve this warn, apply THRIFT-2907.
  - https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2907